# VERY IMPORTANT PERFORMANCE RULES

The new project must be built with **performance-first architecture**.

## FRONTEND PERFORMANCE

Must optimize for:

* very fast dashboard loading
* minimum re-renders
* reusable components
* dynamic imports
* lazy routes
* React.memo
* useMemo
* useCallback
* virtualized large tables
* pagination
* server-side filtering APIs
* debounced search inputs

Do NOT generate unnecessary components.

Keep file structure minimal and professional.

Avoid duplicate files.

Use feature-based architecture.

Example:

src/
modules/
auth/
dashboard/
students/
teachers/
finance/
components/
services/
hooks/
store/
layouts/
routes/
utils/

---

# BACKEND PERFORMANCE

Use modular backend architecture:

backend/
src/
modules/
middleware/
services/
repositories/
routes/
models/
validators/
utils/

Use service layer architecture:

Route → Controller → Service → Repository → Model

All database queries must be optimized.

Use:

* select()
* lean()
* indexes
* pagination
* aggregation where needed
* avoid N+1 query problems

